37#include <config.h>
38#include <krb5/roken.h>
39#include <ctype.h>
40#include <krb5/hex.h>
41
42static const char hexchar[16] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
43
44static int
45pos(char c)
46{
47 const char *p;
48 c = toupper((unsigned char)c);
49 for (p = hexchar; *p; p++)
50 if (*p == c)
51 return p - hexchar;
52 return -1;
53}
54
55ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION ssize_t ROKEN_LIB_CALL
56hex_encode(const void *data, size_t size, char **str)
57{
58 const unsigned char *q = data;
59 size_t i;
60 char *p;
61
62 /* check for overflow */
63 if (size * 2 < size) {
64 *str = NULL;
65 return -1;
66 }
67
68 p = malloc(size * 2 + 1);
69 if (p == NULL) {
70 *str = NULL;
71 return -1;
72 }
73
74 for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
75 p[i * 2] = hexchar[(*q >> 4) & 0xf];
76 p[i * 2 + 1] = hexchar[*q & 0xf];
77 q++;
78 }
79 p[i * 2] = '\0';
80 *str = p;
81
82 return i * 2;
83}
84
85ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION ssize_t ROKEN_LIB_CALL
86hex_decode(const char *str, void *data, size_t len)
87{
88 size_t l;
89 unsigned char *p = data;
90 size_t i;
91
92 l = strlen(str);
93
94 /* check for overflow, same as (l+1)/2 but overflow safe */
95 if ((l/2) + (l&1) > len)
96 return -1;
97
98 if (l & 1) {
99 p[0] = pos(str[0]);
100 str++;
101 p++;
102 }
103 for (i = 0; i < l / 2; i++)
104 p[i] = pos(str[i * 2]) << 4 | pos(str[(i * 2) + 1]);
105 return i + (l & 1);
106}
